====Definitions====
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[carve]] or [[cut]] [[jade]] or [[gemstone]]
#* {{zh-x|玉 不 琢，不 成 器；人 不 學，不 知 道。是故 古 之 王者 建國 君 民，教學 為 先。|If a jade is not '''carved''', it will not become a vessel; if a person does not learn, he will not know the Way. It was thus that when the ancient sovereigns founded their states and ruled the people, they took education as their priority.|ref=Liji}}
# {{lb|zh|by extension}} to [[cultivate]] (one's character, one's skills)
#* {{zh-x|孔 門 弟子 七十 之 徒，皆 任 卿相 之 用，被服 聖教，文才 雕琢，知能 十 倍，教訓 之 功 而 漸漬 之 力 也。|ref=Lunheng|Each of the seventy disciples of Confucius's school served in ministerial roles. They donned the sagely teachings and '''cultivated''' their cultural refinement; their knowledge and ability grew tenfold. This was the result of instruction in the teachings, and the result of gradually becoming saturated [in these teachings].}}

